result.formatted_address: 166 Jockey Club Rd, Sheung Shui, Hong Kong
result.name: Thai Empire

reviews.text: an authentic Thai restaurant with friendly staff, ice cold beer and great food at reasonable prices. the Thai beef salad is outstanding.

I've been here several times over the past year and a half. The food is consistently good and despite other peoples comments on the service,  I've always had good service here. I've eaten at many different Thai places around HK so I have alot to compare this place to and for the price, it would rank very high. The lettuce wrap is very good and you can get it with chicken which is a nice change from the usual pork. The tom yum is very good, could be a bit spicier, but the sour, salt and sweet levels are balanced well. The pork neck is great as is the sauce it comes with. This place is a bit expensive if its not tea time but otherwise its a great experience overall. If your looking for other good Thai places , The Golden Durian in Fanling is also great✌️
Young staffs have no respond to the customers, and the elder staffs are excellent. The Thai Food there is great, with average-high price. Environment is overall nice and clean.
呢間泰國餐廳食過幾次，質素都維持到，不錯的，都坐得舒服。

服務差，出餐慢
𣎴再有下一次
